TEXT(beginproblem());
$showPartialCorrectAnswers = 1;

$a1 = random(1,4,1);
$x1 = random(1,5,1);
$y1 = $a1/$x1**2;
$m1 = -2*$a1/($x1*$x1*$x1);

BEGIN_TEXT
If \( f(x) =  \frac { $a1 } {x^2}  \), find \( f'( $x1 ) \), using the
definition of derivative. \( f'( $x1 ) \) is the limit as \(x\to\) \{ans_rule()\}
of the expression
$BR
\{ans_rule(40)\}
$BR
The value of this limit is
\{ans_rule(20) \}
$BR
END_TEXT

$ans1 = $x1;
$ans2 = "($a1/x**2 - $y1)/(x - $x1)";
$ans = $m1;
ANS(num_cmp($ans1));
ANS(fun_cmp($ans2));
ANS(num_cmp($ans));


